Map Job Profiles to Queues

Use the Workforce Engagement Configuration App to map job profiles to queues for capacity planning in an Omni-Channel queue-based routing workflow.

Workforce Engagement is available in Lightning Experience and requires Enterprise, Performance, or Unlimited Editions. A Workforce Engagement Analyst or Planner permission set is needed to map job profiles and queues.

Mapping job profiles to queues involves:

Associating a job profile with the queue it routes to
Defining capacity settings for the job profile
Defining service level agreements for the job profile

To start, open the Workforce Engagement Configuration App and select Job Profile Mapping from the tree menu. Select the job profiles you want to map, then click Map.

Complete these steps:

1. Click Next.
2. Define job profile capacities: Select a job profile, review or modify capacity settings, and repeat for each profile.
3. Click Next.
4. Define service level agreements: Set field values for each job profile, defining the percentage of support requests to address within a certain timeframe.

Click Done when complete. You can delete job profile-to-queue mappings from the Settings: Workforce Engagement tab.

See Capacity Plan Glossary and other related documentation.
title: Mapping Job Profiles to Queues in Service Cloud
